<< /Length 520 >>
stream
BT /F1 24 Tf 45.00 490.00 Td (10. Parallelism Level) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 440.00 Td (Coarse-grained task-level parallelism.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 416.00 Td (- Each MPI rank runs one independent GA population.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 392.00 Td (- The city data and distance matrix are replicated on every rank.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 368.00 Td (- Different ranks use different random seeds and explore different regions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 344.00 Td (Hybrid task and exploratory decomposition.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
24 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 960 540] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 25 0 R >>
endobj
25 0 obj
<< /Length 524 >>
stream
BT /F1 24 Tf 45.00 490.00 Td (11. Why Exploratory Decomposition?) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 440.00 Td (- A TSP tour is a global permutation, so splitting cities directly is not natural.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 416.00 Td (- GA search is stochastic; multiple populations can search different areas.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 392.00 Td (- Islands can run mostly independently and communicate only occasionally.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 368.00 Td (- This creates coarse granularity and reduces communication frequency.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
26 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 960 540] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 27 0 R >>
endobj
27 0 obj
<< /Length 422 >>
stream
BT /F1 24 Tf 45.00 490.00 Td (12. Process Mapping) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 440.00 Td (- One-dimensional mapping:) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 416.00 Td (- Each rank owns one population and its fitness array.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 392.00 Td (- Cluster hostfile maps ranks round-robin across four machines.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 368.00 Td (- Up to 48 ranks were used, limited by the common physical-core count.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
28 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 960 540] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 29 0 R >>
endobj
29 0 obj
<< /Length 681 >>
stream
BT /F1 24 Tf 45.00 490.00 Td (13. Communication Strategy) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 440.00 Td (- Periodic blocking collective communication.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 416.00 Td (- Every -sync generations:) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 392.00 Td (- each rank finds its local best,) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 368.00 Td (- MPI_Allreduce\(MINLOC\) finds the global best and owner,) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 344.00 Td (- owner broadcasts the best tour with MPI_Bcast,) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 320.00 Td (- other ranks partially migrate this information into local populations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 296.00 Td (- Logical topology: global collective, not ring and not master-slave.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
30 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 960 540] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 31 0 R >>
endobj
31 0 obj
<< /Length 608 >>
stream
BT /F1 24 Tf 45.00 490.00 Td (14. Partial Global-Best Migration) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 440.00 Td (- The owner broadcasts the best tour.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 416.00 Td (- Other islands do not clone the full tour.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 392.00 Td (- They use OX crossover between:) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 368.00 Td (- the global best tour,) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 344.00 Td (- a random local mate.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 320.00 Td (- The child replaces one of the worst local individuals.) Tj ET
BT /F1 15 Tf 60.00 296.00 Td (- Goal: spread good sub-routes while preserving diversity.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
